Performing Arts: one of the biggest and best in NYC offering 3 full concert bands, 2 jazz bands, 2 choral ensembles, 2 dance ensembles, chamber groups such as guitar ensemble, brass choir or clarinet choir, and AP Music Theory. No previous music experience is necessary to join the performing arts. Our program allows students to perform at their ability level regardless of age or experience. Beginning players perform in the Concert Band, intermediate players perform in the Symphonic Band and advanced players perform in the Wind Ensemble. The choral and dance programs offer similar options to the students. All musical ensembles compete annually at the New York State Music Association festival where they have received multiple "Gold" and "Gold with Distinction" awards. Annual theater/musical theater performances by students. We also offer over 20 after-school clubs, Presentations at City/State Conferences, and School Spirit Activities.
Sports: Full program of school sports; students compete in the Grand Street Campus (GSC) Athletic Program. All activities are supported by the GSC Events Staff.

We have three full concert bands, two jazz bands, two choral ensembles, and numerous chamber groups such as guitar ensemble, brass choir or clarinet choir. Students also have the option of taking A.P. Music Theory. While it is very useful, no previous experience is necessary to join the performing arts department. The instrumental and choral programs draw from all three schools in the campus and allow students to perform at their ability level regardless of age or experience. All musical ensembles compete annually at the New York State Music Association festival where they have received multiple "Gold" and "Gold with Distinction" awards.
